  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Web Clipper Chrome Extension for Open Brain Knowledge Capture\n\nBuild a Chrome extension that allows users to clip web page content directly into the Krisp Open Brain knowledge system, transforming any web page into a structured, searchable memory entry — just as Slack captures spoken thoughts, the extension captures discovered knowledge.\n\n---\n\nArchitecture Overview\n\nThe feature spans three layers:\n\n1. Chrome Extension (frontend capture layer)\n2. Krisp API endpoint (ingestion + storage layer)\n3. Open Brain database + MCP (retrieval layer)\n\n---\n\nSub-Tasks\n\n1. Chrome Extension — Content Extraction\n\n- Scaffold a Manifest V3 Chrome extension with a popup UI and a content script\n- Content script extracts clean plain text from the active tab using a Readability-style parsing strategy (strip nav, footer, ads, scripts, and boilerplate; retain meaningful body text, headings, and structure)\n- Capture metadata automatically: page title, canonical URL, domain, and timestamp\n- Allow the user to optionally highlight a selection before clipping — if a selection exists, clip only the highlighted passage rather than the full page\n- Display a small popup with: a preview of the extracted text (truncated), an editable title field (pre-filled with the page title), a tags input field (comma-separated), and a Clip to Krisp button\n- Show success or error state inline in the popup after submission\n\n2. Krisp API — Ingestion Endpoint\n\n- Create a new API route: POST /api/brain/clips\n- Accept payload: { title, url, domain, plain_text, tags[], clipped_at }\n- Authenticate the request using the user's Personal API Key (already exists in the system) passed as a Bearer token in the Authorization header — this allows the extension to work without a browser session\n- Truncate plain_text to a safe maximum (e.g., 12,000 characters) before embedding to stay within token limits; store the full text separately\n- Generate a vector embedding of the plain text using the existing OpenAI Embeddings pipeline (same 1536-dimensional pgvector flow used for emails)\n- Insert a new record into the brain_entries table (or equivalent Open Brain storage table) with source type set to web_clip\n\n3. Database — Schema Extension\n\n- Add a source_type enum value: web_clip (alongside existing values such as slack, manual, etc.)\n- Add a source_url column (text, nullable) to store the origin URL of the clip\n- Add a source_domain column (text, nullable) for domain-level filtering and analytics\n- Ensure the new columns are included in existing MCP retrieval queries and semantic search indexes\n\n4. MCP — Retrieval Awareness\n\n- Update the semantic search tool to surface web_clip entries with their source_url as a citation link in results\n- Update the list recent tool to display web clips with a 🌐 source indicator and the origin domain\n- Update the stats tool to include web_clips as a tracked capture source in pattern analysis\n\n5. Chrome Extension — Authentication Flow\n\n- On first install, display an onboarding screen prompting the user to paste their Krisp Personal API Key (link directly to the key management page in the Krisp app)\n- Store the key securely in chrome.storage.local (never in localStorage or plaintext cookies)\n- Provide a way to update or revoke the stored key from the extension settings panel\n\n6. Krisp UI — Web Clips in the Brain Dashboard\n\n- Display web_clip entries in the Open Brain feed with a distinct clip icon and the source domain shown as a secondary label\n- Make the source URL clickable (opens original page in a new tab)\n- Add web_clip as a filterable source type in any existing brain entry filter controls\n\n---\n\nEdge Cases to Handle\n\n- Pages that block content scripts (e.g., Chrome Web Store, PDF viewer) — show a graceful \"This page cannot be clipped\" message\n- Very long pages — enforce client-side truncation before sending; inform the user if content was trimmed\n- Duplicate clips — if the same URL has already been clipped (check via source_url on the backend), return a warning but still allow the user to save if they confirm\n- No meaningful text extracted — disable the Clip button and show an \"Unable to extract content from this page\" message\n- API key missing or invalid — show a clear authentication error with a link to the Krisp key management page\n- Offline or API unreachable — surface a network error and offer a retry button\n\n---\n\nAcceptance Criteria\n\n- A user can install the extension, authenticate with their API key, visit any standard web page, and clip its content to Krisp in under 15 seconds\n- Clipped entries appear immediately in the Open Brain feed and are semantically searchable via both the Krisp UI and any MCP-connected AI client\n- The MCP semantic search tool returns web clip entries with their source URL as a citation\n- The extension gracefully handles all listed edge cases without crashing or silently failing\n- No user session cookie or password is stored in the extension — authentication relies solely on the Personal API Key",
  "title": "Create Chrome extension for Krisp web content capture",
