  "updatedAt": "2026-03-05T17:19:12.492Z",
  "summary": "## Summary: Web Clipper Chrome Extension for Open Brain Knowledge Capture\n\n### Changes Implemented\n\n**1. Database Schema Extension**\n- Added `sourceUrl` (text, nullable) and `sourceDomain` (varchar 255, nullable) columns to the `brainThoughts` table in `lib/db/schema.ts`\n- Added index `idx_brain_thoughts_source_url` on (userId, sourceUrl) for efficient duplicate URL lookups\n\n**2. Database Migration**\n- Created `drizzle/migrations/0023_add-web-clip-columns.sql` adding the two new columns and index\n\n**3. API Ingestion Endpoint — `POST /api/brain/clips`**\n- Accepts `{ title, url, domain, plain_text, tags[], clipped_at }` payload\n- Authenticates via Personal API Key (Bearer token) using existing `webhookSecrets` table with timing-safe comparison\n- Truncates text to 12,000 chars for embedding, stores full text\n- Generates 1536-dim vector embedding via OpenAI text-embedding-3-small\n- Extracts AI metadata (topic, sentiment, urgency) via OpenRouter\n- Stores as `brain_thoughts` entry with `source: \"web_clip\"`, encrypted content\n- Checks for duplicate URLs and informs client (allows re-clip per spec)\n- CORS headers for cross-origin Chrome extension requests\n- Rate limiting (20 requests/minute/user)\n- Full Zod validation\n\n**4. Brain Chat Context Update**\n- Added `brainThoughts` to the imports and parallel data fetch in `handleBrainQuery`\n- Brain thoughts (including web clips) are now included as context for the AI assistant\n- Web clips show source URL as citation in context\n- Updated system prompt to mention brain thoughts and web clips\n- Added `brain_thoughts` source tracking in sourcesUsed\n\n**5. Brain Dashboard UI Update**\n- Added `brain_thoughts` source badge (teal color) and label to Brain Chat page\n\n**6. Chrome Extension (Manifest V3)**\n- `manifest.json` — Extension config with popup, content script, permissions (activeTab, storage, scripting)\n- `content.js` — Content script that extracts clean text from pages using Readability-style approach (strips nav, footer, ads, etc.), supports user text selection\n- `popup.html` — Full popup UI with setup/onboarding screen and clip form\n- `popup.css` — Clean, modern styling for the popup\n- `popup.js` — Popup logic handling auth flow, content extraction with scripting API fallback, clip submission, success/error states\n- `icons/` — Placeholder PNG icons (16, 48, 128px) with README for proper icon generation\n- Authentication flow: onboarding screen for API key + Krisp URL, stored in chrome.storage.local\n- Settings panel to update/revoke stored credentials\n- Edge case handling: restricted pages, no content, offline, auth errors, duplicate URLs\n\n### Files Modified\n- `lib/db/schema.ts` — Added sourceUrl, sourceDomain columns and index to brainThoughts\n- `app/api/brain/chat/route.ts` — Added brainThoughts import, context fetch, decryption, context building, updated system prompt\n- `app/(app)/brain/page.tsx` — Added brain_thoughts source badge color and label\n\n### Files Created\n- `drizzle/migrations/0023_add-web-clip-columns.sql` — Migration for new columns\n- `app/api/brain/clips/route.ts` — New API endpoint for web clip ingestion\n- `extension/manifest.json` — Chrome extension manifest\n- `extension/content.js` — Content extraction script\n- `extension/popup.html` — Extension popup UI\n- `extension/popup.css` — Popup styles\n- `extension/popup.js` — Popup logic\n- `extension/icons/icon16.png` — Placeholder icon\n- `extension/icons/icon48.png` — Placeholder icon\n- `extension/icons/icon128.png` — Placeholder icon\n- `extension/icons/README.md` — Icon generation instructions\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- Run migration `0023_add-web-clip-columns.sql` against the database before deploying\n- Replace placeholder PNG icons in `extension/icons/` with proper Krisp brain logo icons at 16x16, 48x48, and 128x128 pixels\n- The Chrome extension uses the same Personal API Key (Zapier webhook secret) for authentication — users find their key in Admin > Integrations\n- To install the extension: Chrome > `chrome://extensions` > Enable Developer Mode > Load Unpacked > select the `extension/` directory\n- CORS is set to `*` on the clips endpoint because Chrome extension origins (`chrome-extension://`) are dynamic and cannot be predicted\n- The content script uses a Readability-style approach with a fallback to `chrome.scripting.executeScript` for pages where the content script hasn't loaded yet",
  "justFinishedAt": "2026-03-05T17:19:12.492Z"
}